Download Craigslist Dataset 7


1. Download Craigslist Dataset and SQL Script to Create Data Warehouse Database objects:

a. Download the Zipped file by clicking on the icon  top left of screen. You will find a JSON file for the Craigslist dataset and 3 SQL Scripts for creating Data Warehouse environment and for stored procedures for populating DimDate table for date range 01/01/2010 to 12/31/2030. This date range can be changed by changing the parameters with EXEC command in the 2nd script for calling the stored procedure.  The 3rd script is for creating the AuditLoadFileSTG table and the stored procedure for populating the table as well as the T-SQL EXEC command to be embedded in the SSIS Execute SQL Task that accomplishes this task. This is explained in the script itself.

b. Create a folder for the JSON source file and move it there.

c. Create a folder for archiving JSON source files once loaded into the staging area


2. Create Data Warehouse environment based on the architecture:



Go to SQL Server Management Studio and run the SQL Scripts to create your DW Databases and tables. This creates all the objects, namely, databases, stored procedures, and tables including the date dimension table and the AuditLoadFile for capturing audit information. Run the scripts in Management Studio in the order given below:

·        SQLQueryCreateAllTablesForUsedCarDataWarehouse20200825.sql

·        PopulateDimDate 20200623.sql

·        SQLQueryPopulateAuditFile20200625.sql

Confirm in Management Studio that the objects have been created by right clicking on the Database tab and selecting Refresh and on the VehicleDW, VehicleODS and VehicleSTG tabs and selecting Refresh. See below Screen:







https://www.kaggle.com/austinreese/craigslist-carstrucks-data
